commentTextItems.html: clipped away, maybe a leg bye behind point, and Engerlund win it

commentPostTextItems.html: 3rd ODI win in a row, they better be careful or they might find some form
and poor old Kenya get beaten up again, despite having the support of 190 or so countries in this match
tomorrow's matches are India v Zim and Sri Lanka v South Africa to complete the the second round of group A matches
matches to begin at 945 GMT, pending the miserable English weather

milestones.description: Steve Tikolo and Ravi Shah's 100-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 84 between Otieno and Steve Tikolo
Steve Tikolo has become the top scorer for KENYA in ODIs with 768 runs, going past Otieno's 761
Aasif Karim has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (27) for KENYA, going past Hitesh Modi
